Oh, crap!
I thought this was
your sister's room.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.360
Well, it's not.

12:09.362 --> 12:11.062
Can you tell Dana
I'm here?

12:11.064 --> 12:14.966
Mmm, no. This is kind of
a creepy thing to do, bro.

12:14.968 --> 12:15.900
(WINDOW OPENS)

12:15.902 --> 12:17.235
What the hell's going on
out here?

12:17.237 --> 12:19.204
Nothing, sir.
Go back to bed.

12:19.206 --> 12:20.705
Some weird kid's here
for Dana.

12:20.707 --> 12:22.340
(WINDOW OPENS)
<i>♪ I am complete</i>

12:22.342 --> 12:24.109
Adam? What are you doing?

12:24.111 --> 12:27.178
Adam? This is the kid
who broke your bike?

12:27.180 --> 12:28.813
Yeah.
Not cool, man.

12:28.815 --> 12:30.982
<i>♪ The resolution</i>
<i>You have a lovely home.</i>

12:30.984 --> 12:34.319
(SPRINKLERS HISSING)
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

12:36.122 --> 12:38.389
(MUSIC STOPS)
Pleasure meeting you!

12:38.391 --> 12:39.958
POPS:
<i>Calm down, kiddo.</i>

12:39.960 --> 12:42.093
We can fix this.
We can't!

12:42.095 --> 12:44.963
I serenaded her brother,
I dropped my boombox,

12:44.965 --> 12:47.132
and I soaked
my Lloyd Dobler coat.

12:47.134 --> 12:50.235
I understood none of that.
Did you take my advice?

12:50.237 --> 12:51.436
Yes. A big gesture.

12:51.438 --> 12:54.672
I stood outside her window
and blasted music at her.

12:54.674 --> 12:55.974
Why would you do that?

12:55.976 --> 12:56.508
You told me to!

12:56.510 --> 12:59.410
I meant take her out
for a milkshake.

12:59.412 --> 13:01.546
How is a milkshake
a big gesture?

13:01.548 --> 13:02.313
For you, it's big.

13:02.315 --> 13:04.048
You should have been
more specific!

13:04.050 --> 13:07.285
Wait. Don't go, kiddo.
We can just regroup.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.319
Forget it.

13:08.321 --> 13:10.889
The movies lie.
None of it's real!

13:10.891 --> 13:12.056
Love isn't real.

13:12.058 --> 13:13.758
(MOUTH FULL) Tell that
to my girlfriend.

13:13.760 --> 13:16.294
She's not real!
She's not real!

13:17.329 --> 13:19.264
(BELL DINGS)

13:21.033 --> 13:24.202
All right,
let's get this over with.

13:24.204 --> 13:25.103
One ring, please.

13:25.105 --> 13:28.139
Of course.
Do you have anything
in particular in mind?

13:28.141 --> 13:32.577
Don't look at me.
Just pick something
that speaks to you.

13:32.579 --> 13:33.144
Okay.

13:33.146 --> 13:36.514
All right, uh, this one's
talking up a storm.
How much is it?

13:36.516 --> 13:38.683
That one is $5,000.

13:38.685 --> 13:39.517
Is that the one
I pointed to?

13:39.519 --> 13:40.852
You pointed at that one,
yeah.

13:40.854 --> 13:42.120
It just stopped
speaking to me.

13:42.122 --> 13:43.188
Stopped completely.
Oh, really?

13:43.190 --> 13:44.856
Yeah.
Is that because
I'm not worth the money?

13:44.858 --> 13:46.891
No, no, no, no, no.
Don't do that, Bev.

13:46.893 --> 13:47.892
Don't... Don't do that.
Really?

13:47.894 --> 13:49.360
How much am I worth
to you?

13:49.362 --> 13:51.863
I cannot put a price
on love.

13:51.865 --> 13:55.600
I can. Uh, how much
is this ring worth?

13:55.602 --> 13:58.036
Oh. Very nice.

13:58.170 --> 14:00.638
Yes, excellent cut.
Beautiful clarity.

14:00.640 --> 14:01.739
You must really love
this lady.

14:01.741 --> 14:05.109
It used to belong
to his ex-fiance, Anita.

14:05.111 --> 14:05.777
Oh, add that story.

14:05.779 --> 14:07.378
And he re-gifted it
to me.
All right, do that.

14:07.380 --> 14:08.546
Ugh.
Yeah, and he used to
write her

14:08.548 --> 14:11.249
lots of love letters
and poems.
Oh, yeah, tell him, yeah.

14:11.251 --> 14:13.885
How many do you think
he's written to me?

14:14.453 --> 14:18.356
Um... I'm gonna guess
it's a low number.

14:18.358 --> 14:20.325
Zero.
That's very low.

14:20.327 --> 14:21.593
Yeah.
Okay. That's because

14:21.595 --> 14:26.097
Anita needed love letters
and all that crap
all day long.

14:26.099 --> 14:26.931
It's why we broke up.

14:26.933 --> 14:29.067
That's all I was doing,
was writing letters.

14:29.069 --> 14:30.535
I didn't get to
watch any TV.

14:30.537 --> 14:31.636
Oh, listen to this guy.

14:31.638 --> 14:33.538
He thinks I don't need
love letters.

14:33.540 --> 14:34.772
That's why I chose you.

14:34.774 --> 14:37.141
You don't need any
of that romantic junk.

14:37.143 --> 14:38.943
Oh, that's right.
Just give ol' Bev

14:38.945 --> 14:42.113
a Hallmark Card
and a used ring.

14:42.115 --> 14:43.615
All right,
you know what?

14:43.617 --> 14:45.884
We're gonna get you
the $5,000 ring,

14:45.886 --> 14:47.285
and you can be the one
who tells Adam

14:47.287 --> 14:49.854
that his teeth
are gonna be crooked
for the rest of his life.

14:49.856 --> 14:52.624
Great. That's exactly
what I want, a spite ring.

14:52.626 --> 14:54.225
Great, because that's
what you're getting.

14:54.227 --> 14:57.028
Oh.
Okay, my friend,
we are buying the ring.

14:57.030 --> 14:59.464
I'd like you
to ring it up,

14:59.466 --> 15:01.766
because we are
buying it!

15:01.901 --> 15:03.167
All right.

15:03.169 --> 15:05.303
(MOUTHING WORDS)

15:05.305 --> 15:07.839
(MOUTHS WORD) Um...

15:07.841 --> 15:09.674
(MOUTHING WORDS)

15:09.676 --> 15:10.608
I don't know
what to do here.

15:10.610 --> 15:13.144
You heard the man.
Ring it up.
(MOUTHS WORDS)

15:13.146 --> 15:14.746
All right,
but just so you know,

15:14.748 --> 15:18.349
we have a strict
no return policy.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.385
Ring it up.

15:20.387 --> 15:22.620
(MOUTHING WORDS)

15:23.122 --> 15:24.122
(CLICKS)

15:24.124 --> 15:26.090
(BEVERLY CHUCKLES)

15:32.631 --> 15:35.967
<i>In most houses,</i>
<i>a dinner this quiet</i>
<i>was normal,</i>

15:35.969 --> 15:38.169
<i>but in our house,</i>
<i>no yelling</i>

15:38.171 --> 15:42.106
<i>meant something very bad</i>
<i>was going down.</i>

15:42.108 --> 15:44.509
(LOWERED VOICE)
What's happening?

15:46.412 --> 15:47.745
(LOWERED VOICE)
Dad bought Mom
a spite ring,

15:47.747 --> 15:51.516
and now she's wearing
the spite ring
to spite him.

15:52.718 --> 15:55.520
Lot of love problems
around here.

15:55.522 --> 15:56.988
Not Barry.

15:56.990 --> 15:59.390
I keep my lady satisfied.

15:59.959 --> 16:00.925
Dude...

16:00.927 --> 16:01.993
I was at camp with you.

16:01.995 --> 16:04.228
There's no girl
named Marion Lemieux.

16:04.230 --> 16:07.065
She was in the large-chested
foxy girl bunk,

16:07.067 --> 16:08.900
and you were in
the annoying sister bunk,

16:08.902 --> 16:11.536
so you probably never
crossed paths.

16:11.538 --> 16:12.704
Really?
'Cause I thought you were

16:12.706 --> 16:15.239
in the large-chested
girl bunk.

16:15.241 --> 16:17.642
(CHOMPING) Original.

16:17.644 --> 16:20.945
Adam! Dinner's almost over!

16:20.947 --> 16:23.948
Come on! Get out of
the stupid tree!

16:23.950 --> 16:26.818
ADAM: I'm not hungry!
Go away.

16:26.885 --> 16:28.186
(SIGHS)

16:28.188 --> 16:29.687
(CREAKS)

16:30.889 --> 16:32.557
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

16:32.559 --> 16:33.624
What's going on?

16:33.626 --> 16:35.426
I just wanna be alone,
okay?

16:35.428 --> 16:37.128
Like how I'll be
for the rest of my life.

16:37.130 --> 16:40.431
What are you talking about?
You're 10 years old.

16:40.433 --> 16:42.266
I'm 12. And...

16:42.268 --> 16:44.235
I really screwed things up
with a girl.

16:44.237 --> 16:46.404
Yeah? Tell me about it.

16:46.406 --> 16:47.739
Well, her name's Dana...

16:47.741 --> 16:49.240
No, I didn't mean
"tell me about it"

16:49.242 --> 16:53.344
"tell me about it."
I meant, I screwed up
with a girl, too.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.313
Oh! My gosh.

16:55.315 --> 16:57.248
So is the girl Mom?

16:57.316 --> 16:58.549
Yes, it's Mom!

16:58.551 --> 17:00.952
Your mother seems to think
that I don't show her

17:00.954 --> 17:02.687
that I care about her
enough.

17:02.689 --> 17:04.155
I show her all the time,

17:04.157 --> 17:07.859
just not in big ways,
but in little ways...

17:07.861 --> 17:09.961
You know, ways that
she doesn't notice,

17:09.963 --> 17:11.929
not like a box
of love letters.

17:11.931 --> 17:15.333
There's no record
of the stuff that I do.

17:15.501 --> 17:17.668
You know, maybe there is.

17:17.670 --> 17:18.903
There isn't.
What if there were?

17:18.905 --> 17:22.473
There's not.
Dad, I'm saying
I have an idea.

17:23.575 --> 17:25.710
<i>My dad may not</i>
<i>have been able to say</i>

17:25.712 --> 17:26.644
<i>how he felt about my mom,</i>

17:26.646 --> 17:31.349
<i>but luckily,</i>
<i>I recorded a bunch</i>
<i>of ways that showed it.</i>

17:32.284 --> 17:33.551
(CLICKS AND WHIRS)

17:33.553 --> 17:35.853
<i>(IN YOUR EYES</i> PLAYING)

17:44.396 --> 17:45.997
<i>♪ Love</i>

17:48.667 --> 17:50.868
<i>♪ I get so lost</i>

17:51.470 --> 17:54.272
<i>♪ Sometimes</i>

17:54.940 --> 17:57.975
<i>♪ Days pass</i>

17:59.511 --> 18:02.046
<i>♪ And this emptiness</i>

18:02.048 --> 18:04.849
<i>♪ Fills my heart</i>

18:05.918 --> 18:10.621
<i>♪ When I want to run away</i>

18:10.623 --> 18:15.927
<i>♪ I drive off in my car</i>

18:16.929 --> 18:20.531
<i>♪ But whichever way I go</i>

18:20.533 --> 18:24.669
<i>♪ I come back</i>
<i>to the place you are ♪</i>

18:24.671 --> 18:27.939
ADULT ADAM:
<i>Turns out the most</i>
<i>romantic movie of the '80s</i>

18:27.941 --> 18:30.108
<i>was the one that I made</i>
<i>with my dad.</i>

18:30.110 --> 18:33.778
I hate my new ring.
I'm gonna take it
back tomorrow.

18:33.780 --> 18:36.614
But the man said
no returns.

18:36.616 --> 18:39.784
Eh. I'll guilt him
into it.

18:39.786 --> 18:41.519
It's what I do.

18:41.521 --> 18:43.121
<i>♪ Without my pride</i>

18:43.123 --> 18:47.058
ADULT ADAM:
<i>It was the first time</i>
<i>we ever saw them kiss,</i>

18:47.060 --> 18:48.626
<i>and it was gross.</i>

18:48.628 --> 18:49.927
<i>But I started to believe</i>
<i>in love again.</i>

18:49.929 --> 18:53.698
<i>I mean, it was complicated</i>
<i>as hell, but it was real.</i>

18:53.700 --> 18:57.568
<i>Maybe those romantic movies</i>
<i>weren't so far off after all.</i>

18:57.570 --> 18:59.537
<i>♪ I see the doorway</i>
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

18:59.539 --> 19:02.473
<i>♪ To a thousand churches</i>
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

19:02.475 --> 19:04.775
<i>♪ The resolution</i>
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

19:04.777 --> 19:08.980
<i>♪ Of all</i>
<i>the fruitless searches</i>
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

19:09.348 --> 19:11.716
<i>♪ Oh, I see the light</i>
<i>and the heat ♪</i>

19:11.718 --> 19:14.452
<i>♪ In your eyes,</i>
<i>the light, the heat</i>

19:14.454 --> 19:17.955
<i>♪ Oh, I wanna be</i>
<i>that complete</i>
<i>Me?</i>

19:17.957 --> 19:18.856
Yeah, you.

19:18.858 --> 19:22.226
<i>♪ I wanna touch the light,</i>
<i>the heat</i>

19:22.228 --> 19:25.329
<i>♪ I see in your eyes</i>

19:25.664 --> 19:27.398
Hi.
Hi.

19:29.234 --> 19:32.537
You left this
on our lawn.

19:32.771 --> 19:34.005
Yeah, I...

19:34.007 --> 19:36.340
I did. I'm sorry.

19:37.409 --> 19:39.010
(SIGHS)

19:39.344 --> 19:43.614
The other night
was weird. (CHUCKLES)

19:45.317 --> 19:48.719
You know, my dad told me
not to talk to you anymore.

19:49.321 --> 19:50.521
I... I get it.

19:50.523 --> 19:52.924
Too bad I never listen
to my dad.

19:53.025 --> 19:54.725
(EXHALES)

19:56.628 --> 19:58.496
<i>♪ And all my instincts</i>

19:58.498 --> 19:59.931
Wanna go for a ride?

19:59.933 --> 20:01.666
<i>♪ They return</i>

20:01.668 --> 20:04.202
<i>♪ And the grand facade</i>

20:04.204 --> 20:05.036
<i>♪ So soon will burn</i>

20:05.038 --> 20:09.140
Just like I told him...
Go big or go home.

20:09.142 --> 20:13.344
Yeah. Think you can
help me out
with some girl stuff?

20:13.346 --> 20:15.947
Oh. What happened
to Miss Canada?

20:15.949 --> 20:17.848
Long distance. It's...
It's killing us.

20:17.850 --> 20:20.818
We never talk,
and when we do,
we fight.

20:20.820 --> 20:22.420
She's not real.

20:23.755 --> 20:26.424
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

20:27.492 --> 20:29.961
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

20:30.162 --> 20:32.730
<i>♪ In your eyes</i>

20:35.234 --> 20:38.469
ADAM:
<i>There goes the fluffage,</i>
<i>different directions.</i>

20:38.471 --> 20:39.337
<i>Is that like a bald spot?</i>

20:39.339 --> 20:40.805
<i>Yeah, yeah, we do have</i>
<i>a bald spot there.</i>

20:40.807 --> 20:43.774
(RECORD NEEDLE SCRATCHES)
(BELL DINGS)

20:50.582 --> 20:52.950
(BEVERLY'S VOICE)  <i>Murray!</i>

20:53.752 --> 20:55.286
What?

20:55.621 --> 20:56.754
Murray!

20:56.756 --> 20:59.056
What? Ugh!

21:00.859 --> 21:02.627
<i>Murray!</i>

21:03.495 --> 21:05.196
What's going on?

21:05.198 --> 21:07.331
<i>Murray!</i>
<i>What?</i>

21:07.966 --> 21:09.967
<i>Murray!</i>
<i>What? Wh...</i>

21:09.969 --> 21:11.035
<i>Murray!</i>

21:11.037 --> 21:11.802
Well, where are you?

21:11.804 --> 21:13.504
(VOICE RAISING PITCH)
<i>Murray, Murray!</i>

21:13.506 --> 21:14.939
What?

21:14.941 --> 21:15.439
<i>Murray!</i>

21:15.441 --> 21:17.642
What do you want
from me, woman?

21:17.644 --> 21:19.777
(CHUCKLES)
Technology.

21:19.779 --> 21:22.780
(LOWERED VOICE) I know.
I love this thing.

21:22.782 --> 21:24.749
Hey!
(KEYBOARD CLATTERS)

21:24.751 --> 21:25.816
I see you!

21:25.818 --> 21:26.917
(RAPID FOOTSTEPS DEPART)

21:26.919 --> 21:28.586
What'd you break?
